pageContext.claim: “And you have to treat our people great. I think the vaccines are coming quickly. I do think it's somewhat political... I think they'd like to do it after the election, even if it's a couple of days. But the fact is, the vaccines are coming out. The therapeutics are coming out.”
pageContext.analysis: There is no evidence that the development of a vaccine was delayed for political reasons or because of the election. Ironically, the process went faster than expected because the U.S. caseload was so high.
